  "prompt": "What is the average wage for a graduate engineer in Belgium?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, the average salary for a graduate engineer in Belgium typically ranges from \u20ac35,000 to \u20ac55,000 per year, depending on various factors such as the specific engineering discipline, the region in which they work, and the size of the company. \n\nIt's important to note that entry-level positions may start at the lower end of this range, while those with some experience or specialized skills may earn more. For the most accurate and up-to-date information, checking salary surveys or reports specific to the engineering field in Belgium would be beneficial.",
